strate the theoretical perspectives from globally relevant research spaces and traditions. Both established and future scholars can benefit from the handbook’s fresh approach to writing in the context of multimodal, multi-semiotic text production.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCommunication and technologyvHandbooks, manuals, etc. 0aWritten communicationvHandbooks, manuals, etc. 0aWritten communicationxStudy and teachingvHandbooks, manuals, etc. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aApplied Linguistics, Textproduction, Communication, Writing.1 aAndersen, Jack, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAntos, Gerd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBazerman, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeaufort, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerkenkotter, Carol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDale, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDevitt, Amy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDonahue, Christiane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGnach, Aleksandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrésillon, Almuth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHicks, Troy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIñesta, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacobs, Geert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJakobs, Eva-Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJakobs, Eva-Maria, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/